## Summary

The migration from PatternFly 5 to PatternFly 6 was nearly complete — the automated tools had already updated imports, components, props, and CSS tokens correctly. The only remaining step was updating the **package.json dependency versions** to point to PatternFly 6 packages and regenerating the lock file.

### Change Made

**`web/package.json`** — Updated PatternFly dependency versions:

| Package | Before (PF5) | After (PF6) |
|---------|-------------|-------------|
| `@patternfly/react-core` | `^5.1.1` | `^6.5.1` |
| `@patternfly/react-icons` | `^5.1.1` | `^6.5.1` |
| `@patternfly/react-topology` | `^6.2.0` | `^6.5.0` |

Then ran `npm install` to update `package-lock.json` to be consistent with the new dependencies.

